text: Fabian Holzer (born 28 July 1992) is a German male badminton player. In 2011, he won the silver medal in the boys' doubles event at the European Junior Championships partnered with Max Schwenger, and in 2016, he won the men's doubles title at the Brazil Open Grand Prix tournament with Michael Fuchs. == Achievements == ===European Junior Championships=== Boys' Doubles {|class="sortable wikitable" style="font-size: 95%;" !|Year !|Venue !|Partner !|Opponent !|Score !|Result |- style="background:#AABBCC" |align="center"|2011 |align="left"|Vantaan Energia Arena, Vantaa, Finland |align="left"| Max Schwenger |align="left"| Chris Coles Matthew Nottingham |align="left"|21–15, 14–21, 15–21 |style="text-align:left; background:white" |Silver Silver |} === BWF Grand Prix === The BWF Grand Prix has two level such as Grand Prix and Grand Prix Gold. It is a series of badminton tournaments, sanctioned by Badminton World Federation (BWF) since 2007.
